==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Participate
<hw>Par*tic"i*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>participatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>participare</ets> to participate;
<ets>pars</ets>, <ets>partis</ets>, part + <ets>capere</ets> to take.
See <er>Part</er>, and <er>Capacious</er>.]</ety> <def>Acting in common;
participating.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Participate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Participate
<hw>Par*tic"i*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Participated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Participating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To have a share in common
with others; to take a part; to play a role; to partake; -- followed by
<ptcl>in</ptcl>, formerly by <ptcl>of</ptcl>; <as>as, to
<ex>participate</ex> in a debate; to <ex>participate</ex> in a
discussion</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So would he <qex>participate</qex> of their wants.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mine may come when men⟦br⟧
With angels may <qex>participate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Participate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Participate
<hw>Par*tic"i*pate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To partake
of; to share in; to receive a part of.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fit to <qex>participate</qex> all rational delight.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To impart, or give, or share of.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>participating</ent>⟦br⟧
